s=usertitle>Team Skald Member</span><br>  Posts: 21<br> <font color=#ff0000>(5/17/02 4:00:02 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=99.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re-evaluate Skald Epic armor.</span><hr size=1> I'll make this short and sweet.<br><br>It gives too much + str and not enough +cha.<br>I'm easily capped out (+40 over) on strength, this epic gives way too much strength and not nearly enough charisma.<br><br>Also the + to BS is utterly useless at the moment, a statement from Mythic declaring their intentions regarding + BS items would be most appreciated!<br>--<br><br>As for Fury of the Gods, I seriously believe that skill should be re-hashed. Either an insanely drastic increase to damage and duration, say +50% damage to counteract cleric for 60 seconds (Clerics absorb buff can not be affected by variables such as blade turn.) and a timer of 30 minutes..<br><br>or wipe it and give us something more skald like.<br><br>The damage add just feels like a hasty patch in to me =(. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/ushikang.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Shikang</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#ff0000>(5/17/02 5:58:47 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=99.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Re-evaluate Skald Epic armor.</span><hr size=1> I would really like some change to to the stats of the epic too just look at this url to compare it to the other midgard epics, our epic stats really are the worst atm. <br><br><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.yeggs.net/underfoot/cgi-bin/yabb/YaBB.cgi?board=general_news;action=display;num=1018462954">www.yeggs.net/underfoot/c...1018462954</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br><br>Epic will cap most people str and con easily i personnaly would like to see some more dex on it next to cha too.(for crits/evade/parry)<br>The only melee resist we get is a 10% thrust resist i really would like to see some slash and crush resists too on it.<br>There is 8% matter resist and if you look here:<br><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.yeggs.net/underfoot/cgi-bin/yabb/YaBB.cgi?board=general_rvr;action=display;num=1017328285">www.yeggs.net/underfoot/c...1017328285</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>That matter resist is only useful for the cab dot spell and a sorc dot spell.<br><br>There is 0% heat resist on epic and a massive 20% cold resist on it in total kinda badly balanced to me imo since half of offensive spells from alb and hib are heat and cold resist. Most skald will have their cold resist maxed and heat very low now.<br><br>Also 5+ battlesongs on armor which has proven is just as useful for skald as +chants for paladins(zilch).<br>And last but not least zero weapon or parry stats on armor.<br>(i'm wearing my ebon gloves over epic now because of that which give +3 to axe/hammer/sword and +4parry)<br><br>Rosey? <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <br><br> <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/ushikang.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Shikang</A> at: 5/17/02 6:04:47 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/uraenwynde.showPublicProfile?language=EN>raenwynde</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 13<br> <font color=#ff0000>(5/17/02 10:47:32 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=99.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Re-evaluate Skald Epic armor.</span><hr size=1> Please ask for Thrust resist on it... if there is one thing missing in Midgard its decent Thrust resist gear....<br><br>I agree that the Str. and Con as well as BS are over emphasised in our epic, and would like to see some of that redistributed to other areas that would make more of a difference to us such as resists e.g. Fire, Thrust, Maybe Crush, Matter for starters...<br><br><br>Grnok <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/udarkith.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Darkith</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Member</span><br>  Posts: 72<br> <font color=#ff0000>(5/17/02 10:49:55 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=99.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://asgarthvanguard.com/images/avcrest.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Re-evaluate Skald Epic armor.</span><hr size=1> Actually the Skald epic sleeves have 10% Thrust Resist.  I think it is the highest thrust resist item in the game. <p>-----------------------------------<br><b>Darkith - lvl 50 Troll Skald</b><br><a href="http://asgarthvanguard.com"><b>[ Asgarth's Vanguard ]</b></a><br><b>Iseult</b></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/ubristolltheskald.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bristolltheskald</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Participant</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#ff0000>(6/16/02 4:18:34 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=99.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Re-evaluate Skald Epic armor.</span><hr size=1> Yeah! That!<br><br>Rosey,<br><br>Think you could see what you could do about informing mythic that the STR and CON bonuses are TOO strong and get maybe some QUI and DEX and CHA bonuses for us 2H (most) players? =)<br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=dane>Dane</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Participant</span><br>  Posts: 12<br> <font color=#ff0000>(6/17/02 4:03:08 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=99.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Re-evaluate Skald Epic armor.</span><hr size=1> The armor itself gives us ONLY +5 Battlesongs.  This is not balanced.<br><br>Voice and note (Necklace and jewel slots) give us another +3 battlesong, and +3 parry.<br><br>So we get +3 parry, a very low bonus, and +8 battlesong which currently does zip.<br><br>WE NEED MORE PARRY AND WE NEED WEAPONSKILL BONUS ON OUR EPIC.  We should have at least one piece with +3/hammer/sword/axe.  Most people drop the gloves for barbed ebon gloves (+4parry/+3 s/h/axe) since we get jack on our epic.<br><br>Lowering STR in favor of more CHA was also a great suggestion.<br><br>-Dane <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showPrevMessage?topicID=99.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showNextMessage?topicID=99.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=99.topic&index=5><img src=http://www.stuckathome.com/skalded/images/addreply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0>